Cape Verdeâ€™s external borders are closed and international flights are suspended. There are currently no commercial options available to leave Cape Verde.
If you cannot leave Cape Verde at this time, see advice on staying in Cape Verde during coronavirus.
UK special flight
Booking for the UK special flight to return to the UK from 3 June has now closed. There are currently no further special flights organised from Cape Verde.
This travel advice will be updated with further information on any other options to leave Cape Verde as soon as this is available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Future Options
We do not plan any further UK government special flights from Cape Verde after 3 June. We are in contact with airlines, the Cape Verdean authorities and other governments to make sure commercial options for returning to the UK are available as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
A small number of European repatriation flights may still occasionally operate. If you are a UK visitor, normally resident in the UK, and you would like to express your interest in an EU repatriation flights, you should use this form stating your name and which island you are on.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options available to you for getting funds you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
Travel to the airport
Amilcar Cabral International Airport, Sal is located near the town of Espargos. The airport is easily accessible from any part of the island.
Taxis and airport shuttles are available
You will need to wear a face mask and follow local laws such as limited numbers in taxis and any other local instructions
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
If you are returning home before 8 June, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others. From 8 June there will be new rules for entering the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy in Lisbon, Portugal, on +351 21 392 4000. The Embassy in Lisbon provides consular support to Cape Verde.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
